Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Classes
  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Constructors
  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    org.embulk.spi.type.AbstractType
    Plugins should not refer this class directly.
    org.embulk.spi.time.Timestamp
    Use Instant instead as much as possible.
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.embulk.spi.Buffer.allocate(int)
    This method is to be removed. Plugins should no longer call it directly.
    org.embulk.spi.Page.allocate(int)
    It is to be removed, implemented only for compatibility. Plugins should no longer call it directly.
    org.embulk.spi.Buffer.array()
    Accessing the internal byte array is not safe.
    org.embulk.spi.Buffer.copyOf(byte[])
    This method is to be removed. Plugins should no longer call it directly.
    org.embulk.spi.Buffer.copyOf(byte[], int, int)
    This method is to be removed. Plugins should no longer call it directly.
    org.embulk.spi.json.JsonValue.fromMsgpack(Value)
    Do not use this method. It is to be removed at some point after Embulk v1.0.0. It is here only to ensure a migration period from MessagePack-based JSON values to new JSON values of JsonValue.
    org.embulk.spi.type.Type.getFixedStorageSize()
    It would be removed in Embulk v0.10 or v0.11. Do not use it.
    org.embulk.spi.type.TimestampType.getFormat()
    org.embulk.spi.type.Type.getJavaType()
    It would be removed in Embulk v0.10 or v0.11. Do not use it.
    org.embulk.spi.type.AbstractType.getJavaType()
    org.embulk.spi.PageReader.getJson(Column)
    Use PageReader.getJsonValue(org.embulk.spi.Column) instead.
    org.embulk.spi.PageReader.getJson(int)
    Use PageReader.getJsonValue(int) instead.
    org.embulk.spi.Exec.getLogger(Class<?>)
    Call LoggerFactory.getLogger(Class) directly, instead.
    org.embulk.spi.ExecSession.getLogger(Class<?>)
    Call LoggerFactory.getLogger(Class) directly, instead.
    org.embulk.spi.Exec.getLogger(String)
    Call LoggerFactory.getLogger(String) directly, instead.
    org.embulk.spi.ExecSession.getLogger(String)
    Call LoggerFactory.getLogger(String) directly, instead.
    org.embulk.spi.ExecSession.getSessionExecConfig()
    Plugins should no longer use it. It would be removed.
    org.embulk.spi.Page.getStringReferences()
    Do not call this method directly from plugins.
    org.embulk.spi.PageReader.getTimestamp(Column)
    Use PageReader.getTimestampInstant(Column) instead.
    org.embulk.spi.PageReader.getTimestamp(int)
    Use PageReader.getTimestampInstant(int) instead.
    org.embulk.spi.Exec.getTransactionTime()
    Timestamp is deprecated.
    org.embulk.spi.ExecSession.getTransactionTime()
    Timestamp is deprecated.
    org.embulk.spi.Page.getValueReference(int)
    Use Page.getJsonValueReference(int) instead.
    org.embulk.spi.Page.getValueReferences()
    Do not call this method directly from plugins.
    org.embulk.config.ConfigSource.loadConfig(Class<T>)
    Use embulk-util-config instead.
    org.embulk.config.TaskSource.loadTask(Class<T>)
    Use embulk-util-config instead.
    org.embulk.spi.Exec.newConfigDiff()
    Recommended to start using embulk-util-config from plugins. Use its own newConfigDiff.
    org.embulk.spi.ExecSession.newConfigDiff()
    Recommended to start using embulk-util-config from plugins. Use its own newConfigDiff.
    org.embulk.spi.Exec.newConfigSource()
    Recommended to start using embulk-util-config from plugins. Use its own newConfigSource.
    org.embulk.spi.ExecSession.newConfigSource()
    Recommended to start using embulk-util-config from plugins. Use its own newConfigSource.
    org.embulk.spi.Exec.newTaskReport()
    Recommended to start using embulk-util-config from plugins. Use its own newTaskReport.
    org.embulk.spi.ExecSession.newTaskReport()
    Recommended to start using embulk-util-config from plugins. Use its own newTaskReport.
    org.embulk.spi.Exec.newTaskSource()
    Recommended to start using embulk-util-config from plugins. Use its own newTaskSource.
    org.embulk.spi.ExecSession.newTaskSource()
    Recommended to start using embulk-util-config from plugins. Use its own newTaskSource.
    org.embulk.spi.Exec.session()
    Plugins are discouraged from getting the ExecSession instance.
    org.embulk.spi.PageBuilder.setJson(Column, Value)
    Use PageBuilder.setJson(org.embulk.spi.Column, org.embulk.spi.json.JsonValue) instead.
    org.embulk.spi.PageBuilder.setJson(int, Value)
    Use PageBuilder.setJson(int, org.embulk.spi.json.JsonValue) instead.
    org.embulk.spi.Page.setStringReferences(List<String>)
    Do not call this method directly from plugins.
    org.embulk.spi.PageBuilder.setTimestamp(Column, Timestamp)
    org.embulk.spi.PageBuilder.setTimestamp(int, Timestamp)
    org.embulk.spi.Page.setValueReferences(List<ImmutableValue>)
    Do not call this method directly from plugins.

  • Deprecated Constructors 
    Constructor and Description
    org.embulk.spi.Buffer(byte[], int, int)
    org.embulk.spi.PageBuilder(BufferAllocator, Schema, PageOutput)
    The constructor is deprecated although Embulk v0.9-compatible plugins still have to use this. See GitHub Issue #1321: Deprecate PageBuilder's constructor for the details.
    org.embulk.spi.PageReader(Schema)
    The constructor is deprecated although Embulk v0.9-compatible plugins still have to use this. See GitHub Issue #1323: Deprecate PageReader's constructor for the details.

    The constructor is no longer available. Use Exec.getTempFileSpace() instead.
